  "text": "XPCOM Component Implementation Guide\n\nThis implementation demonstrates Firefox XPCOM component patterns based on analysis of the Mozilla Firefox codebase.\n\n## Key Files Referenced\n\n### Core XPCOM Infrastructure (xpcom/base/nsISupportsImpl.h)\nThe nsISupportsImpl.h file contains critical macros for XPCOM reference counting:\n- NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS: Declares QueryInterface, AddRef, and Release methods\n- NS_DECL_THREADSAFE_ISUPPORTS: Thread-safe variant using ThreadSafeAutoRefCnt\n- NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS: Implements the reference counting interface methods\n- These macros handle the automatic implementation of XPCOM's COM-style reference counting\n\n### Component Factory (xpcom/components/ModuleUtils.h)\nThe ModuleUtils.h file provides factory constructors:\n- NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR: Creates a simple constructor that instantiates the class and calls QueryInterface\n- NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR_INIT: Constructor variant that calls an initialization method\n- NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_SINGLETON_CONSTRUCTOR: For singleton components\n\n### Observer Service Examples\n\n1. nsObserverService (xpcom/ds/nsObserverService.h/cpp):\n   - Implements nsIObserverService which manages observers\n   - Uses NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS and NS_DECL_NSIOBSERVERSERVICE macros\n   - Implements NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS with multiple interfaces (nsIObserverService, nsIMemoryReporter)\n   - Shows the pattern for implementing XPCOM components\n\n2. RestoreTabContentObserver (toolkit/components/sessionstore/):\n   - Implements nsIObserver interface\n   - Uses NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS and NS_DECL_NSIOBSERVER macros\n   - Uses NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS macro to implement the interface methods\n   - Demonstrates observer registration/unregistration with nsIObserverService\n\n3. Database (toolkit/components/places/Database.h):\n   - Uses NS_DECL_THREADSAFE_ISUPPORTS for thread-safe reference counting\n   - Implements multiple interfaces (nsIObserver, nsSupportsWeakReference)\n   - Shows how to handle complex initialization with weak references\n\n### Component Registration\n\nThe toolkit/components/build/nsToolkitCompsModule.cpp demonstrates:\n- Custom constructor functions that retrieve singleton instances\n- Following the factory constructor pattern for component registration\n- Integration with the Mozilla component manager\n\n## Implementation Pattern\n\nThe SampleComponent files implement the standard XPCOM pattern:\n\n**Header File (SampleComponent.h):**\n- Includes nsIObserver.h and nsISupportsImpl.h\n- Defines a class inheriting from nsIObserver\n- Uses NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS macro to declare reference counting methods\n- Uses NS_DECL_NSIOBSERVER macro to declare the Observe method\n- Defines a CID (Class ID) using a UUID\n\n**Implementation File (SampleComponent.cpp):**\n- Uses NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS macro to implement QueryInterface, AddRef, Release\n- Implements the Observe method from nsIObserver\n- Uses NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR macro to generate the factory function\n- Registers the component with contract ID and CID in the module structure\n- Uses NSMODULE_DEFN to export the module\n\n## Key Concepts\n\n1. **Reference Counting**: NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS declares mRefCnt member and methods; NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS implements them\n2. **Interface Implementation**: NS_DECL_NSIOBSERVER declares the Observe method; NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS handles interface discovery\n3. **Factory Pattern**: NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR creates a constructor function that follows the XPCOM factory pattern\n4. **Component Registration**: Components are registered with a contract ID (@mozilla.org/...) and CID (UUID) for discovery\n5. **Thread Safety**: Use NS_DECL_THREADSAFE_ISUPPORTS for components accessed from multiple threads"
}

